The paper deals with lower bounds on monotone projections of polynomials, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The reduction used in the paper involves extended formulations of polytopes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the Hamiltonian Cycle polynomial, cut polynomials, and perfect matching polynomial, which are all related to graph theory (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds on monotone formula size and monotone circuit size, which are topics in machine learning and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
